                <head>184. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On January 7, the White House announced that President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> had appointed <persName
                        corresp="#p_RJP1">James P. Richards</persName> as Special Assistant to the
                    President with the personal rank of Ambassador to advise and assist the
                    President and the Secretary of State on problems of the Middle Eastern area. In
                    particular, <persName>Richards</persName> was commissioned to head a special
                    group of Department of State, Department of Defense, and International
                    Cooperation Administration officials to implement certain aspects of U.S. Middle
                    Eastern policies. For text of the announcement, see Department of State <hi
                        rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, January 28, 1957, page 130.</p>
            </div>
